Thomas B. (Tom) Cusick 

		
		EVP, Finance and CFO, 

	
		 Columbia Sportswear Company 	

 
Last Updated: 09/01/2015 



Executive Summary
Cusick serves as the Chief Financial Officer of Columbia Sportswear Company, a leading manufacturer and distributor of outerwear and sportswear. He joined Columbia in September 2002 as Corporate Controller and was named Vice President and Corporate Controller in March 2006. He was promoted to VP, CFO and Treasurer in January 2009, and  
Current Focus
Company Snapshot:  Columbia Sportswear Company manufactures and distributes outerwear and sportswear. It was founded in 1938 by the late Paul Lamfrom, father of present Chairman Gert Boyle. The Company is headquarte 
Biographical Highlights

Born circa 1967.
Cusick earned a Bachelor’s degree in Business from the University of Idaho in 1990. 
Other Boards and Organizations

Member, Business Advisory Council, School of Business Administration, Portland State University 

 





